## 7. Conclusion and Future Scope
### Conclusion
The EcoSched simulator successfully demonstrates that integrating hardware-level awareness (DVFS and Thermal) into the operating system scheduler can yield substantial energy savings (often 20-40% compared to Round Robin) without sacrificing the ability to meet real-time task deadlines. The use of ML-based prediction further optimizes the power profile by smoothing out frequency transitions.

### Future Scope
*   **Multi-Core Heterogeneous Support**: Implementing support for ARM-style big.LITTLE architectures (Performance vs. Efficiency cores).
*   **Advanced ML Models**: Replacing EWMA with Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) or LSTMs for complex workload pattern recognition.
*   **Process Priority Aging**: Implementing aging to prevent starvation in low-priority tasks during high thermal stress.

